    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A synthetic green-blue pigment made by fixing barium manganate on a barium sulfate base. It is an inert pigment that can range in color from a clear azure blue to a bright emerald green. Manganese blue was first discovered in 1907 but not patented until 1935.</Note_Text>
